# Casual cover message style

Cover / stego carrier text should read like casual conversation about everyday things, and must continue the ongoing chat cohesively.

When editing prompts (`chain_system`, `prompt`, `carrierReplyInstruction`, semantic judge, sentence refresh):

- Prefer texting vibe: contractions, half-thoughts, everyday slang
- Broaden available topics beyond day/weather/work, but stay on the current conversational thread
- React to, answer, or build on prior transcript messages; do not jump topics unless the chat just started
- Same-sender follow-ups advance one coherent thought with new content (multi-cover coherence)
- Keep opener variety rules
- Update `conversation-stenography.local.json` when changing defaults so local runs match
- Peers must share the same generative prompt config or decode breaks

# How-it-works docs

When expanding `website/` educational content, prefer concrete worked examples and the core teaching point: ciphertext bits select among the model’s top next-token candidates; they are not painted into the letters.